  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">European Youth Advocates Against Islamophobia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">60 young people - 10 young people in the UK.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Involvement of young people in advocating against Islamophobia:
-	to engage young people, Muslim and non-Muslim, in advocating against Islamophobia as a human rights violation,
-	to develop young people&#x2019;s understanding of how policies and decisions are made and give them the skills and tools to engage in decision-making processes that affect their lives,
-	to demystify national and European policy making for youth and help them to see how normal citizens can participate and have an influence,
-	to address frustration and exclusion felt by Muslim youth by giving them practical tools to express their needs and advocate for their rights.

Develop Policy-focused advocacy strategies against Islamophobia 
-	to develop strategic policy-oriented approaches to tackling Islamophobia, with clear well-defined policy targets and objectives,
-	to introduce more effective systems for recording and reporting acts of Islamophobia in official higher educational institutes,
-	to enable young people to propose and advocate for solutions in terms of policies changes.

Build cross community trust, partnerships and networks: 
-	to promote exchange of experience between different movements and communities against discrimination and sharing of tools and strategies they developed in different contexts,
-	to build alliances between communities, human rights organisations and other concerned bodies to work for equality and build trust between them,
-	to build solidarity between young people and examine Islamophobia as a shared problem for all members of society,
-	to generate cross-European and cross-community cooperation on combatting Islamophobia as a human rights violation of concern to all society.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To train 60 young people, Muslim and non-Muslim, on how to advocate against Islamophobia. To give them an understanding of Islamophobia as a form of structural discrimination, with specific focus on the higher education sector, and to train them in skills to advocate for policy measures to address Islamophobia in higher education on a national level.</narrative>
  </description>
